gs":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Seynthice de Saint Luce was born in 1147, in Huntingdonshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Avicia de Sculcotes. He died after 1185, in Sculcoates, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1147–Aft 1185":"1147–pärast 1185","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1190–1228":"1190–1228","1147–1185":"1147–1185","1228":"1228","1190":"1190","1147":"1147","Aft 1185":"pärast 1185","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","Huntingdonshire, England":"Huntingdonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sculcotes, Yorkshire, England":"Sculcoates, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1147–Aft 1185":"1147–1185 jälkeen","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1190–1228":"1190–1228","1147–1185":"1147–1185","1228":"1228","1190":"1190","1147":"1147","Aft 1185":"1185 jälkeen","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","Huntingdonshire, England":"Huntingdonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sculcotes, Yorkshire, England":"Sculcoates, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1147–Aft 1185":"1147–après 1185","1140–Female":"1140–Décédée","1190–1228":"1190–1228","1147–1185":"1147–1185","1228":"1228","1190":"1190","1147":"1147","Aft 1185":"après 1185","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","Huntingdonshire, England":"Huntingdonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Sculcotes, Yorkshire, England":"Sculcoates, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","life